7/*
8 * Must come first to avoid warnings on Windows.
9 *
10 * Flex-generated scanners may only include <inttypes.h> if __STDC_VERSION__
11 * is defined with a value >= 199901, meaning "full C99", and MSVC may not
12 * define it with that value, because it isn't 100% C99-compliant, even
13 * though it has an <inttypes.h> capable of defining everything the Flex
14 * scanner needs.
15 *
16 * We, however, will include it if we know we have an MSVC version that has
17 * it; this means that we may define the INTn_MAX and UINTn_MAX values in
18 * scanner.c, and then include <stdint.h>, which may define them differently
19 * (same value, but different string of characters), causing compiler warnings.
20 *
21 * If we include it here, and they're defined, that'll prevent scanner.c
22 * from defining them. So we include <pcap/pcap-inttypes.h>, to get
23 * <inttypes.h> if we have it.
24 */
25#include <pcap/pcap-inttypes.h>
26

435/* Return all but the first "n" matched characters back to the input stream. */
436#define yyless(n) \
437 do \
438 { \
439 /* Undo effects of setting up yytext. */ \
440 int yyless_macro_arg = (n); \
441 YY_LESS_LINENO(yyless_macro_arg);\
442 *yy_cp = yyg->yy_hold_char; \
443 YY_RESTORE_YY_MORE_OFFSET \
444 yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yy_cp = yy_bp + yyless_macro_arg - YY_MORE_ADJ; \
445 YY_DO_BEFORE_ACTION; /* set up yytext again */ \
446 } \
447 while ( 0 )
448#define unput(c) yyunput( c, yyg->yytext_ptr , yyscanner )

450#ifndef YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE
451#define YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE
452struct yy_buffer_state
453 {
454 FILE *yy_input_file;
455
456 char *yy_ch_buf; /* input buffer */
457 char *yy_buf_pos; /* current position in input buffer */
458
459 /* Size of input buffer in bytes, not including room for EOB
460 * characters.
461 */
462 size_t yy_buf_size;
463
464 /* Number of characters read into yy_ch_buf, not including EOB
465 * characters.
466 */
467 size_t yy_n_chars;
468
469 /* Whether we "own" the buffer - i.e., we know we created it,
470 * and can realloc() it to grow it, and should free() it to
471 * delete it.
472 */
473 int yy_is_our_buffer;
474
475 /* Whether this is an "interactive" input source; if so, and
476 * if we're using stdio for input, then we want to use getc()
477 * instead of fread(), to make sure we stop fetching input after
478 * each newline.
479 */
480 int yy_is_interactive;
481
482 /* Whether we're considered to be at the beginning of a line.
483 * If so, '^' rules will be active on the next match, otherwise
484 * not.
485 */
486 int yy_at_bol;
487
488 int yy_bs_lineno; /**< The line count. */
489 int yy_bs_column; /**< The column count. */
490
491 /* Whether to try to fill the input buffer when we reach the
492 * end of it.
493 */
494 int yy_fill_buffer;
495
496 int yy_buffer_status;
497
498#define YY_BUFFER_NEW 0
499#define YY_BUFFER_NORMAL 1
500 /* When an EOF's been seen but there's still some text to process
501 * then we mark the buffer as YY_EOF_PENDING, to indicate that we
502 * shouldn't try reading from the input source any more. We might
503 * still have a bunch of tokens to match, though, because of
504 * possible backing-up.
505 *
506 * When we actually see the EOF, we change the status to "new"
507 * (via yyrestart()), so that the user can continue scanning by
508 * just pointing yyin at a new input file.
509 */
510#define YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING 2
511
512 };
513#endif /* !YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE */
514
515/* We provide macros for accessing buffer states in case in the
516 * future we want to put the buffer states in a more general
517 * "scanner state".
518 *
519 * Returns the top of the stack, or NULL.
520 */
521#define YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ( yyg->yy_buffer_stack \
522 ? yyg->yy_buffer_stack[yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top] \
523 : NULL)
524/* Same as previous macro, but useful when we know that the buffer stack is not
525 * NULL or when we need an lvalue. For internal use only.
526 */
527#define YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE yyg->yy_buffer_stack[yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top]

4616/* yy_get_next_buffer - try to read in a new buffer
4617 *
4618 * Returns a code representing an action:
4619 * EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH -
4620 * EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN - continue scanning from current position
4621 * EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE - end of file
4622 */
4623static int yy_get_next_buffer (yyscan_t yyscanner)
4624{
4625 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
4626 char *dest = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf;
4627 char *source = yyg->yytext_ptr;
4628 yy_size_t number_to_move, i;
4629 int ret_val;
4630
4631 if ( yyg->yy_c_buf_p > &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars + 1] )
4632 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
4633 "fatal flex scanner internal error--end of buffer missed" );
4634
4635 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_fill_buffer == 0 )
4636 { /* Don't try to fill the buffer, so this is an EOF. */
4637 if ( yyg->yy_c_buf_p - yyg->yytext_ptr - YY_MORE_ADJ == 1 )
4638 {
4639 /* We matched a single character, the EOB, so
4640 * treat this as a final EOF.
4641 */
4642 return EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
4643 }
4644
4645 else
4646 {
4647 /* We matched some text prior to the EOB, first
4648 * process it.
4649 */
4650 return EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
4651 }
4652 }
4653
4654 /* Try to read more data. */
4655
4656 /* First move last chars to start of buffer. */
4657 number_to_move = (yy_size_t) (yyg->yy_c_buf_p - yyg->yytext_ptr - 1);
4658
4659 for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
4660 *(dest++) = *(source++);
4661
4662 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
4663 /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
4664 * just force an EOF
4665 */
4666 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars = 0;
4667
4668 else
4669 {
4670 yy_size_t num_to_read =
4671 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
4672
4673 while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
4674 { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
4675
4676 /* just a shorter name for the current buffer */
4677 YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE;
4678
4679 int yy_c_buf_p_offset =
4680 (int) (yyg->yy_c_buf_p - b->yy_ch_buf);
4681
4682 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
4683 {
4684 yy_size_t new_size = b->yy_buf_size * 2;
4685
4686 if ( new_size <= 0 )
4687 b->yy_buf_size += b->yy_buf_size / 8;
4688 else
4689 b->yy_buf_size *= 2;
4690
4691 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *)
4692 /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
4693 yyrealloc( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf,
4694 (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) , yyscanner );
4695 }
4696 else
4697 /* Can't grow it, we don't own it. */
4698 b->yy_ch_buf = NULL;
4699
4700 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
4701 YY_FATAL_ERROR(
4702 "fatal error - scanner input buffer overflow" );
4703
4704 yyg->yy_c_buf_p = &b->yy_ch_buf[yy_c_buf_p_offset];
4705
4706 num_to_read = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size -
4707 number_to_move - 1;
4708
4709 }
4710
4711 if ( num_to_read > YY_READ_BUF_SIZE )
4712 num_to_read = YY_READ_BUF_SIZE;
4713
4714 /* Read in more data. */
4715 YY_INPUT( (&YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move]),
4716 yyg->yy_n_chars, num_to_read );
4717
4718 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars;
4719 }
4720
4721 if ( yyg->yy_n_chars == 0 )
4722 {
4723 if ( number_to_move == YY_MORE_ADJ )
4724 {
4725 ret_val = EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
4726 yyrestart( yyin , yyscanner);
4727 }
4728
4729 else
4730 {
4731 ret_val = EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
4732 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buffer_status =
4733 YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING;
4734 }
4735 }
4736
4737 else
4738 ret_val = EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN;
4739
4740 if ((yyg->yy_n_chars + number_to_move) > YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size) {
4741 /* Extend the array by 50%, plus the number we really need. */
4742 yy_size_t new_size = yyg->yy_n_chars + number_to_move + (yyg->yy_n_chars >> 1);
4743 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyrealloc(
4744 (void *) YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf, (yy_size_t) new_size , yyscanner );
4745 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf )
4746 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_get_next_buffer()" );
4747 /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
4748 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_size = (yy_size_t) (new_size - 2);
4749 }
4750
4751 yyg->yy_n_chars += number_to_move;
4752 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
4753 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars + 1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
4754
4755 yyg->yytext_ptr = &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[0];
4756
4757 return ret_val;
4758}

4760/* yy_get_previous_state - get the state just before the EOB char was reached */
4761
4762 static yy_state_type yy_get_previous_state (yyscan_t yyscanner)
4763{
4764 yy_state_type yy_current_state;
4765 char *yy_cp;
4766 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
4767
4768 yy_current_state = yyg->yy_start;
4769
4770 for ( yy_cp = yyg->yytext_ptr + YY_MORE_ADJ; yy_cp < yyg->yy_c_buf_p; ++yy_cp )
4771 {
4772 YY_CHAR yy_c = (*yy_cp ? yy_ec[YY_SC_TO_UI(*yy_cp)] : 1);
4773 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
4774 {
4775 yyg->yy_last_accepting_state = yy_current_state;
4776 yyg->yy_last_accepting_cpos = yy_cp;
4777 }
4778 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
4779 {
4780 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
4781 if ( yy_current_state >= 1729 )
4782 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
4783 }
4784 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
4785 }
4786
4787 return yy_current_state;
4788}
4789
4790/* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
4791 *
4792 * synopsis
4793 * next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
4794 */
4795 static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans (yy_state_type yy_current_state , yyscan_t yyscanner)
4796{
4797 int yy_is_jam;
4798 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner; /* This var may be unused depending upon options. */
4799 char *yy_cp = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
4800
4801 YY_CHAR yy_c = 1;
4802 if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
4803 {
4804 yyg->yy_last_accepting_state = yy_current_state;
4805 yyg->yy_last_accepting_cpos = yy_cp;
4806 }
4807 while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
4808 {
4809 yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
4810 if ( yy_current_state >= 1729 )
4811 yy_c = yy_meta[yy_c];
4812 }
4813 yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c];
4814 yy_is_jam = (yy_current_state == 1728);
4815
4816 (void)yyg;
4817 return yy_is_jam ? 0 : yy_current_state;
4818}

4820#ifndef YY_NO_UNPUT
4821
4822#endif
4823
4824#ifndef YY_NO_INPUT
4825#ifdef __cplusplus
4826 static int yyinput (yyscan_t yyscanner)
4827#else
4828 static int input (yyscan_t yyscanner)
4829#endif
4830
4831{
4832 int c;
4833 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
4834
4835 *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yy_hold_char;
4836
4837 if ( *yyg->yy_c_buf_p == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
4838 {
4839 /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
4840 * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
4841 * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
4842 */
4843 if ( yyg->yy_c_buf_p < &YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_ch_buf[yyg->yy_n_chars] )
4844 /* This was really a NUL. */
4845 *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = '\0';
4846
4847 else
4848 { /* need more input */
4849 yy_size_t offset = (int) (yyg->yy_c_buf_p - yyg->yytext_ptr);
4850 ++yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
4851
4852 switch ( yy_get_next_buffer( yyscanner ) )
4853 {
4854 case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
4855 /* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
4856 * sees that we've accumulated a
4857 * token and flags that we need to
4858 * try matching the token before
4859 * proceeding. But for input(),
4860 * there's no matching to consider.
4861 * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
4862 * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
4863 */
4864
4865 /* Reset buffer status. */
4866 yyrestart( yyin , yyscanner);
4867
4868 /*FALLTHROUGH*/
4869
4870 case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
4871 {
4872 if ( yywrap( yyscanner ) )
4873 return 0;
4874
4875 if ( ! yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof )
4876 YY_NEW_FILE;
4877#ifdef __cplusplus
4878 return yyinput(yyscanner);
4879#else
4880 return input(yyscanner);
4881#endif
4882 }
4883
4884 case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
4885 yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yytext_ptr + offset;
4886 break;
4887 }
4888 }
4889 }
4890
4891 c = *(unsigned char *) yyg->yy_c_buf_p; /* cast for 8-bit char's */
4892 *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = '\0'; /* preserve yytext */
4893 yyg->yy_hold_char = *++yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
4894
4895 return c;
4896}
4897#endif /* ifndef YY_NO_INPUT */

4899/** Immediately switch to a different input stream.
4900 * @param input_file A readable stream.
4901 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
4902 * @note This function does not reset the start condition to @c INITIAL .
4903 */
4904 void yyrestart (FILE * input_file , yyscan_t yyscanner)
4905{
4906 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
4907
4908 if ( ! YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ){
4909 yyensure_buffer_stack (yyscanner);
4910 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE =
4911 yy_create_buffer( yyin, YY_BUF_SIZE , yyscanner);
4912 }
4913
4914 yy_init_buffer( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER, input_file , yyscanner);
4915 yy_load_buffer_state( yyscanner );
4916}
4917
4918/** Switch to a different input buffer.
4919 * @param new_buffer The new input buffer.
4920 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
4921 */
4922 void yy_switch_to_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer , yyscan_t yyscanner)
4923{
4924 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
4925
4926 /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
4927 * with
4928 * yypop_buffer_state();
4929 * yypush_buffer_state(new_buffer);
4930 */
4931 yyensure_buffer_stack (yyscanner);
4932 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
4933 return;
4934
4935 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
4936 {
4937 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
4938 *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yy_hold_char;
4939 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
4940 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars;
4941 }
4942
4943 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
4944 yy_load_buffer_state( yyscanner );
4945
4946 /* We don't actually know whether we did this switch during
4947 * EOF (yywrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
4948 * is looked at is after yywrap() is called, so it's safe
4949 * to go ahead and always set it.
4950 */
4951 yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof = 1;
4952}
4953
4954static void yy_load_buffer_state (yyscan_t yyscanner)
4955{
4956 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
4957 yyg->yy_n_chars = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars;
4958 yyg->yytext_ptr = yyg->yy_c_buf_p = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos;
4959 yyin = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_input_file;
4960 yyg->yy_hold_char = *yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
4961}

4963/** Allocate and initialize an input buffer state.
4964 * @param file A readable stream.
4965 * @param size The character buffer size in bytes. When in doubt, use @c YY_BUF_SIZE.
4966 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
4967 * @return the allocated buffer state.
4968 */
4969 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_create_buffer (FILE * file, yy_size_t size , yyscan_t yyscanner)
4970{
4971 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
4972
4973 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) , yyscanner );
4974 if ( ! b )
4975 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
4976
4977 b->yy_buf_size = size;
4978
4979 /* yy_ch_buf has to be 2 characters longer than the size given because
4980 * we need to put in 2 end-of-buffer characters.
4981 */
4982 b->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyalloc( (yy_size_t) (b->yy_buf_size + 2) , yyscanner );
4983 if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
4984 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
4985
4986 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
4987
4988 yy_init_buffer( b, file , yyscanner);
4989
4990 return b;
4991}
4992
4993/** Destroy the buffer.
4994 * @param b a buffer created with yy_create_buffer()
4995 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
4996 */
4997 void yy_delete_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b , yyscan_t yyscanner)
4998{
4999 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5000
5001 if ( ! b )
5002 return;
5003
5004 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ) /* Not sure if we should pop here. */
5005 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) 0;
5006
5007 if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
5008 yyfree( (void *) b->yy_ch_buf , yyscanner );
5009
5010 yyfree( (void *) b , yyscanner );
5011}

5013/* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
5014 * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
5015 * such as during a yyrestart() or at EOF.
5016 */
5017 static void yy_init_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b, FILE * file , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5018
5019{
5020 int oerrno = errno;
5021 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5022
5023 yy_flush_buffer( b , yyscanner);
5024
5025 b->yy_input_file = file;
5026 b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
5027
5028 /* If b is the current buffer, then yy_init_buffer was _probably_
5029 * called from yyrestart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
5030 * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
5031 */
5032 if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
5033 b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
5034 b->yy_bs_column = 0;
5035 }
5036
5037 b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
5038
5039 errno = oerrno;
5040}

5042/** Discard all buffered characters. On the next scan, YY_INPUT will be called.
5043 * @param b the buffer state to be flushed, usually @c YY_CURRENT_BUFFER.
5044 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
5045 */
5046 void yy_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5047{
5048 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5049 if ( ! b )
5050 return;
5051
5052 b->yy_n_chars = 0;
5053
5054 /* We always need two end-of-buffer characters. The first causes
5055 * a transition to the end-of-buffer state. The second causes
5056 * a jam in that state.
5057 */
5058 b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
5059 b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
5060
5061 b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
5062
5063 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
5064 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
5065
5066 if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
5067 yy_load_buffer_state( yyscanner );
5068}
5069
5070/** Pushes the new state onto the stack. The new state becomes
5071 * the current state. This function will allocate the stack
5072 * if necessary.
5073 * @param new_buffer The new state.
5074 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
5075 */
5076void yypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5077{
5078 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5079 if (new_buffer == NULL)
5080 return;
5081
5082 yyensure_buffer_stack(yyscanner);
5083
5084 /* This block is copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
5085 if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
5086 {
5087 /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
5088 *yyg->yy_c_buf_p = yyg->yy_hold_char;
5089 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_buf_pos = yyg->yy_c_buf_p;
5090 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE->yy_n_chars = yyg->yy_n_chars;
5091 }
5092
5093 /* Only push if top exists. Otherwise, replace top. */
5094 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
5095 yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top++;
5096 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = new_buffer;
5097
5098 /* copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
5099 yy_load_buffer_state( yyscanner );
5100 yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof = 1;
5101}
5102
5103/** Removes and deletes the top of the stack, if present.
5104 * The next element becomes the new top.
5105 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
5106 */
5107void yypop_buffer_state (yyscan_t yyscanner)
5108{
5109 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5110 if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
5111 return;
5112
5113 yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER , yyscanner);
5114 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
5115 if (yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top > 0)
5116 --yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top;
5117
5118 if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
5119 yy_load_buffer_state( yyscanner );
5120 yyg->yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof = 1;
5121 }
5122}
5123
5124/* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
5125 * Guarantees space for at least one push.
5126 */
5127static void yyensure_buffer_stack (yyscan_t yyscanner)
5128{
5129 yy_size_t num_to_alloc;
5130 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5131
5132 if (!yyg->yy_buffer_stack) {
5133
5134 /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
5135 * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
5136 * immediate realloc on the next call.
5137 */
5138 num_to_alloc = 1; /* After all that talk, this was set to 1 anyways... */
5139 yyg->yy_buffer_stack = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyalloc
5140 (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
5141 , yyscanner);
5142 if ( ! yyg->yy_buffer_stack )
5143 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
5144
5145 memset(yyg->yy_buffer_stack, 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
5146
5147 yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max = num_to_alloc;
5148 yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top = 0;
5149 return;
5150 }
5151
5152 if (yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top >= (yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max) - 1){
5153
5154 /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
5155 yy_size_t grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
5156
5157 num_to_alloc = yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max + grow_size;
5158 yyg->yy_buffer_stack = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrealloc
5159 (yyg->yy_buffer_stack,
5160 num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
5161 , yyscanner);
5162 if ( ! yyg->yy_buffer_stack )
5163 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
5164
5165 /* zero only the new slots.*/
5166 memset(yyg->yy_buffer_stack + yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max, 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
5167 yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max = num_to_alloc;
5168 }
5169}

5171/** Setup the input buffer state to scan directly from a user-specified character buffer.
5172 * @param base the character buffer
5173 * @param size the size in bytes of the character buffer
5174 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
5175 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
5176 */
5177YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_buffer (char * base, yy_size_t size , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5178{
5179 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
5180
5181 if ( size < 2 ||
5182 base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
5183 base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
5184 /* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
5185 return NULL;
5186
5187 b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc( sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) , yyscanner );
5188 if ( ! b )
5189 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_buffer()" );
5190
5191 b->yy_buf_size = (size - 2); /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
5192 b->yy_buf_pos = b->yy_ch_buf = base;
5193 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 0;
5194 b->yy_input_file = NULL;
5195 b->yy_n_chars = b->yy_buf_size;
5196 b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
5197 b->yy_at_bol = 1;
5198 b->yy_fill_buffer = 0;
5199 b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
5200
5201 yy_switch_to_buffer( b , yyscanner );
5202
5203 return b;
5204}

5206/** Setup the input buffer state to scan a string. The next call to yylex() will
5207 * scan from a @e copy of @a str.
5208 * @param yystr a NUL-terminated string to scan
5209 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
5210 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
5211 * @note If you want to scan bytes that may contain NUL values, then use
5212 * yy_scan_bytes() instead.
5213 */
5214YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_string (const char * yystr , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5215{
5216
5217 return yy_scan_bytes( yystr, strlen(yystr) , yyscanner);
5218}
5219
5220/** Setup the input buffer state to scan the given bytes. The next call to yylex() will
5221 * scan from a @e copy of @a bytes.
5222 * @param yybytes the byte buffer to scan
5223 * @param _yybytes_len the number of bytes in the buffer pointed to by @a bytes.
5224 * @param yyscanner The scanner object.
5225 * @return the newly allocated buffer state object.
5226 */
5227YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_bytes (const char * yybytes, yy_size_t _yybytes_len , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5228{
5229 YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
5230 char *buf;
5231 yy_size_t n;
5232 yy_size_t i;
5233
5234 /* Get memory for full buffer, including space for trailing EOB's. */
5235 n = (yy_size_t) (_yybytes_len + 2);
5236 buf = (char *) yyalloc( n , yyscanner );
5237 if ( ! buf )
5238 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_bytes()" );
5239
5240 for ( i = 0; i < _yybytes_len; ++i )
5241 buf[i] = yybytes[i];
5242
5243 buf[_yybytes_len] = buf[_yybytes_len+1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
5244
5245 b = yy_scan_buffer( buf, n , yyscanner);
5246 if ( ! b )
5247 YY_FATAL_ERROR( "bad buffer in yy_scan_bytes()" );
5248
5249 /* It's okay to grow etc. this buffer, and we should throw it
5250 * away when we're done.
5251 */
5252 b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
5253
5254 return b;
5255}

5444/* User-visible API */
5445
5446/* yylex_init is special because it creates the scanner itself, so it is
5447 * the ONLY reentrant function that doesn't take the scanner as the last argument.
5448 * That's why we explicitly handle the declaration, instead of using our macros.
5449 */
5450int yylex_init(yyscan_t* ptr_yy_globals)
5451{
5452 if (ptr_yy_globals == NULL){
5453 errno = EINVAL;
5454 return 1;
5455 }
5456
5457 *ptr_yy_globals = (yyscan_t) yyalloc ( sizeof( struct yyguts_t ), NULL );
5458
5459 if (*ptr_yy_globals == NULL){
5460 errno = ENOMEM;
5461 return 1;
5462 }
5463
5464 /* By setting to 0xAA, we expose bugs in yy_init_globals. Leave at 0x00 for releases. */
5465 memset(*ptr_yy_globals,0x00,sizeof(struct yyguts_t));
5466
5467 return yy_init_globals ( *ptr_yy_globals );
5468}
5469
5470/* yylex_init_extra has the same functionality as yylex_init, but follows the
5471 * convention of taking the scanner as the last argument. Note however, that
5472 * this is a *pointer* to a scanner, as it will be allocated by this call (and
5473 * is the reason, too, why this function also must handle its own declaration).
5474 * The user defined value in the first argument will be available to yyalloc in
5475 * the yyextra field.
5476 */
5477int yylex_init_extra( YY_EXTRA_TYPE yy_user_defined, yyscan_t* ptr_yy_globals )
5478{
5479 struct yyguts_t dummy_yyguts;
5480
5481 yyset_extra (yy_user_defined, &dummy_yyguts);
5482
5483 if (ptr_yy_globals == NULL){
5484 errno = EINVAL;
5485 return 1;
5486 }
5487
5488 *ptr_yy_globals = (yyscan_t) yyalloc ( sizeof( struct yyguts_t ), &dummy_yyguts );
5489
5490 if (*ptr_yy_globals == NULL){
5491 errno = ENOMEM;
5492 return 1;
5493 }
5494
5495 /* By setting to 0xAA, we expose bugs in
5496 yy_init_globals. Leave at 0x00 for releases. */
5497 memset(*ptr_yy_globals,0x00,sizeof(struct yyguts_t));
5498
5499 yyset_extra (yy_user_defined, *ptr_yy_globals);
5500
5501 return yy_init_globals ( *ptr_yy_globals );
5502}
5503
5504static int yy_init_globals (yyscan_t yyscanner)
5505{
5506 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5507 /* Initialization is the same as for the non-reentrant scanner.
5508 * This function is called from yylex_destroy(), so don't allocate here.
5509 */
5510
5511 yyg->yy_buffer_stack = NULL;
5512 yyg->yy_buffer_stack_top = 0;
5513 yyg->yy_buffer_stack_max = 0;
5514 yyg->yy_c_buf_p = NULL;
5515 yyg->yy_init = 0;
5516 yyg->yy_start = 0;
5517
5518 yyg->yy_start_stack_ptr = 0;
5519 yyg->yy_start_stack_depth = 0;
5520 yyg->yy_start_stack = NULL;
5521
5522/* Defined in main.c */
5523#ifdef YY_STDINIT
5524 yyin = stdin;
5525 yyout = stdout;
5526#else
5527 yyin = NULL;
5528 yyout = NULL;
5529#endif
5530
5531 /* For future reference: Set errno on error, since we are called by
5532 * yylex_init()
5533 */
5534 return 0;
5535}
5536
5537/* yylex_destroy is for both reentrant and non-reentrant scanners. */
5538int yylex_destroy (yyscan_t yyscanner)
5539{
5540 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5541
5542 /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
5543 while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
5544 yy_delete_buffer( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER , yyscanner );
5545 YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE = NULL;
5546 yypop_buffer_state(yyscanner);
5547 }
5548
5549 /* Destroy the stack itself. */
5550 yyfree(yyg->yy_buffer_stack , yyscanner);
5551 yyg->yy_buffer_stack = NULL;
5552
5553 /* Destroy the start condition stack. */
5554 yyfree( yyg->yy_start_stack , yyscanner );
5555 yyg->yy_start_stack = NULL;
5556
5557 /* Reset the globals. This is important in a non-reentrant scanner so the next time
5558 * yylex() is called, initialization will occur. */
5559 yy_init_globals( yyscanner);
5560
5561 /* Destroy the main struct (reentrant only). */
5562 yyfree ( yyscanner , yyscanner );
5563 yyscanner = NULL;
5564 return 0;
5565}

5601void *yyrealloc (void * ptr, yy_size_t size , yyscan_t yyscanner)
5602{
5603 struct yyguts_t * yyg = (struct yyguts_t*)yyscanner;
5604 (void)yyg;
5605
5606 /* The cast to (char *) in the following accommodates both
5607 * implementations that use char* generic pointers, and those
5608 * that use void* generic pointers. It works with the latter
5609 * because both ANSI C and C++ allow castless assignment from
5610 * any pointer type to void*, and deal with argument conversions
5611 * as though doing an assignment.
5612 */
5613 return realloc(ptr, size);
5614}

5633/* Hex digit to integer. */
5634static inline int
5635xdtoi(int c)
5636{
5637 if (isdigit(c))
5638 return c - '0';
5639 else if (islower(c))
5640 return c - 'a' + 10;
5641 else
5642 return c - 'A' + 10;
5643}
5644
5645/*
5646 * Convert string to integer. Just like atoi(), but checks for
5647 * preceding 0x or 0 and uses hex or octal instead of decimal.
5648 */
5649static int
5650stoi(char *s)
5651{
5652 int base = 10;
5653 int n = 0;
5654
5655 if (*s == '0') {
5656 if (s[1] == 'x' || s[1] == 'X') {
5657 s += 2;
5658 base = 16;
5659 }
5660 else {
5661 base = 8;
5662 s += 1;
5663 }
5664 }
5665 while (*s)
5666 n = n * base + xdtoi(*s++);
5667
5668 return n;
5669}
